      "content": "You are pointing to a powerful historical trend where nationalism has indeed been weaponized for exclusion. While some academic circles debate the possibility, a form of nationalism that is purely non-problematic is very difficult to define. True, inclusive forms of nationalism—which celebrate shared culture while actively welcoming diversity—are rare in practice. Often, the very definition of \"nation\" becomes an inherently exclusive category that requires \"othering\" others to maintain its perceived purity.",
